■ Hand evolution—Choose a water creature in your hand and put this creature into the battle zone on top of that creature.
{TRIPLE BREAKER}
■ This creature can't be blocked.

{DOUBLE BREAKER}
■ At the end of your turn, draw a card, then you and your opponent play Gachinko Judge. If you win, you may cast a water spell from your hand that costs the same as or less than the number of cards in your hand for no cost.
(Gachinko Judge: Each player reveals the top card of their deck, then puts it on the bottom. You win if your card costs the same as or more than your opponent.)

